  <front>
   <head>The Beau to the Virtuosos; alluding to a Proposal for the Publication of a Set of BUTTERFLIES.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">HAIL curious wights, to whom so fair</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">The form of mortal !</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who deem those grubs beyond compare,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">Which  sense despises.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whether your prey, in gardens found,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">Be urg'd thro' walks and allies;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whether o'er hill, morass or mound,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">You make more desperate sallies;</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Amid the fury of the chace,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">No rocks could e'er retard you;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Blest, if a fly repay the race,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">Or painted wing reward you.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Twas thus Camilla, o'er the plain,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">Pursu'd the glittering stranger;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Still ey'd the purple's pleasing stain,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">And knew not fear nor danger.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis you dispense the fav'rite meat</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">To nature's filmy people;</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Know what conserves they chuse to eat,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">And what  to tipple.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis you protect their pregnant hour;</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">And when the birth's at hand,</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Exerting your obstetric pow'r,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">Prevent a mothless land.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Yet oh! my friends! howe'er your view</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">Above gross objects rises;</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whate'er refinements you pursue,</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">Hear what a beau advises.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="8" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A beau, that, weigh'd with your's, must prize</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">Domitian's idle passion;</l>
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who sought the  of teazing flies</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">And not their</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="9" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="33" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Let *****'s eyes more deeply warm,</l>
     <l n="34" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">Nor foolishly determine</l>
     <l n="35" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To slight fair Nature's loveliest form,</l>
     <l n="36" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">And sigh for Nature's vermin.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="10" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="37" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And speak with  respect of beaux;</l>
     <l n="38" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">No more, as triflers, :</l>
     <l n="39" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis better learn to save one's cloaths,</l>
     <l n="40" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="7">Than cherish moths that .</l>
    </lg>
